I'm glad that in a market plagued by crappy apps that costs 6-10$ each, MS manages to make a great game, with a very modest price tag.

Controls are simple, gameplay is easy and entertaining.

My only 2 gripes:
1- Turning sound off in the games options still plays sounds on both the splash screen and title screen.
2- The game seems obsessed with being oriented with the home button being to the right. I orient my tablet with the home to the right (most comfortable due to the case I have), and it correctly orients. As soon as I move it the slightest bit, it goes back to the way it wants to be. Simply annoying.
Once again a incomplete game rushed into the market... Don't get me wrong it's a good game just needs more work.

This game is amazing and is a great game for science-fiction game lovers!!! And it doesn't stop there, when I thought it couldn't get better, I got dog eat dog for another dollar. Let me tell ya, this game is totally worth the $2. Thank you for this amazing game! Please continue the updates that improve this game and make it what it is! I REALLY recommend this game for sci-fi lovers!

If you enjoy anatomy & physiology, you'll love this exploration of the "evil"  Professor Pluff's body.  Much like the classic movie"Fantastic Voyage", you must work your way through varies body systems, to reach your goal.  Animation is high quality & enjoyable to look at & play within the created environment.  And such a cheap price compared to some games, you really get a lot for your dollar.
